description:
Stunning garden floor 1 bedroom apt. in historic, legal 2-family townhouse in Sugar Hill/Harlem/Washington Heights.  Owners (Gay married couple) and several cats rescued from the garden live upstairs.

Ideal pièd-à-terre for the right mature person. Back room is studio with kitchen, queen bed, dining/work table. We (Gay married couple) live upstairs and use the same exit/entrance. We also take our cats down for a walk in the early evening and to the garden weather permitting.  Bathroom and kitchen are private.

Guests have access to the garden floor, the basement, and the garden.  They do not have access to the upper floors of the house.  There is a land line and private wifi with a washer/dryer in the basement.

Guests have their own bath, fully equipped kitchen, and privacy on the floor most of the time.  We do go to the garden or the basement or take the cats for a walk daily.  The housekeeper comes every Tuesday to clean.

This section of Manhattan was built up in the late 1800's to the 1920's.  Stunning architecture, Riverside park, Highbridge park, Jumel Mansion, Audubon Terrace, and the George Washington Bridge are just some of the sites in easy walking distance.  Area is gentrifying rapidly.

Excellent transportation options. #1 train at 157th and 168th St.  C train at 161st/Amsterdam.  A/C trains at 168th St.  #2,3,4,5 Buses.  Easy access to zip car and West Side Highway, George Washington Bridge.  20 minutes to LGA by taxi.  Uber. There is a parking garage (fee) on the block a few doors down.  The ride to Lincoln center on the #1 is 20 minutes--about 30 minutes door to door.

Ideally looking for someone regular who needs a place in Manhattan a few days per week.
